%gra:	1|2|NSUBJ 2|0|ROOT 3|5|CASE 4|5|DET 5|2|OBL 6|2|PUNCT
@Comment:	Time is 0:31
@Comment:	Chi and Mot are enthusiastic about reading the book. Chi reads along pretty well; her errors suggest she's using context as a crutch a lot. On Saturday page Mot tells Chi before she starts to read the words , not the pictures. Mot helps Chi by giving her the initial sounds of words , or by telling her the word , or by semantic clues. Mot asks Chi to point to the egg on the leaf. Argh! Context notes say that at times Mot guides Chi's finger to the next word. Mot is very encouraging. Mot points out rhyme of sister and Christa , and refers to opposites a few times , once inaccurately. That Chi has a lot more trouble with the end of the book is either due to not being able to predict what each word is , or to fatigue.
